    <div class="wl-widget-item">
        <h1 id="pagewidgets">Page widgets</h1>
        <p>Page widgets are those that appear on pages like a Sakai document. For example, content comments, embed content, Google maps and discussions are all page widgets that appear in a Sakai document:</p>
        <%= image_tag "developer_pagewidget_1.png", :alt => "Page widget example" %>

        <hr class="wl-hidden wl-push"/>
        <p>A page widget can be added, removed or moved within its containing page. Another special characteristic of a page widget is that its settings have a separate overlay dialog. This settings dialog can be accessed through the page editor.</p>

        <p><strong>Access a widget's settings by selecting the widget in the page editor and choosing settings. Change and apply the settings by pressing the save button:</strong></p>
        <%= image_tag "developer_pagewidget_2.png", :alt => "Accessing a page widget's settings" %>

        <p><strong>You can add, remove and move page widgets in the page editor. To add a widget to a page, simply drag and drop the widget from the Inserter Bar onto the page:</strong></p>
        <%= image_tag "developer_pagewidget_3.png", :alt => "Adding a page widget via drag and drop" %>

        <p class="wl-bold">The page now includes the widget that you've dropped in:</p>
        <%= image_tag "developer_pagewidget_4.png", :alt => "Page including new widget that was dropped in" %>
    </div>

